<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7240] Cleanup old snapshots on start</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7240</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the master is hard stopped (i.e. kill -9), the snapshot handler or SnapshotManager may not have a chance to cleanup after the snapshot, leaving extraneous files in the working snapshot directory (/hbase/.snapshot/.tmp directory).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12618232">HBASE-7240</key>
            <summary>Cleanup old snapshots on start</summary>
